TopicTitle: [1.3.0] [Kopernicus] Interstellar Adventure Revived v1.2.9 - A Taste of the Upcoming Grand Update! [18August17]

Articles.Content:
***Some unknown forces of the Universe (the Kraken) took down to original thread. I was waiting for it to be restored, but that doesn't seem to be the case. Either way, here's the new thread!***

Interstellar Adventure Revived (IA-Revived) is a continuation of the mod "Interstellar Adventure" by @amarius1. The pack adds in a total of 5 new solar systems, each one a near-realistic representation of their counterparts in our universe. These system are TRAPPIST-1, HD 219134, Mu Arae, K2-3, and PSR-B1257+12. Throughout all systems are 6 stars, 20 planets, 16 moons, and a comet. There are also two additional rogue planets, one inspired by Planet 9. Every object is named and presented in a realistic scale - all values are comparable to Earth but shrunk down to Kerbal scale.

All the planets have been given a Kerbal flare to them to make them more interesting. Whether it's in their appearances or moons (all of which are hypothetical), these objects are more interesting but still very similar to their real-life counterparts.

 

MUST be run in KSP x64-bit!

List of Objects:

ROGUE PLANETS

Spoiler
  • SELPHAR: Large, rogue "Super-Kerbin" orbiting between Kerbol and Niobe. It has a surface rich in weird chemicals that react to cosmic rays and UV radiation. As a result, this world is a multicolored rock. 70% more gravity than Kerbin, but NO ATMOSPHERE.
    • YARKU: Medium-sized desert moon with an atmosphere.
  • BRACIACA: Frozen Duna-sized planemo much further out than Selphar. Kind of looks like cotton candy. The icy surface is coated with a frozen-out atmosphere.

 

TRAPPIST-1

Spoiler
  • TRAPPIST-1: A very popular and tiny ultracool M8.2V red dwarf star. It is only about 2,200 km larger in radius than Jool with only 8% the mass of Kerbol. All 7 planets in real life are added.
    • THEROS: Trappist-1b, a volcanic Kerbin-sized planet with an oddly low density. It is theorized to not have an iron core, due to metals and rock mixing together during formation. Theros has a thick atmosphere similar to that of Eve, except less hot and less dense.
    • AUXO: Trappist-1c, an iron-rich desert planet. It is just a tad larger than Theros but has nearly 1.4x the mass of Kerbin. Therefore, it means Auxo is dominated by an iron core taking up 50% of its volume.
    • THALLO: Trappist-1d, the most Kerbin-like planet ever found (even more so than Lamancha) and the first potentially habitable sub-Kerbin. It has an oxygen rich atmosphere, small seas, and a desert-like landscape dotted with photosynthetic bacteria. A large ice cap dominates the back side.
    • EIAR: Trappist-1e, another incredibly Kerbin-like planet. It is just a tad smaller than Kerbin and is home to PURPLE plants, not green ones. That's because life needs to be a darker color here to absorb enough light to survive. Has a large ice cap and a VERY purple atmosphere.
    • IRENE: Trappist-1f, the first potentially habitable ocean planet. It is 25% water by volume and mostly covered by a huge back side ice cap.
    • CARPHOs: Trappist-1g, an unusually green planet at the edge of the habitable zone, and the final ocean-covered world in the system. While Carpho seems to be an ocean planet, it actually has small islands, along with land masses just below the water. That green coloring - similar to that of Minmus - is unexplained.
    • CHEIMON: Trappist-1h, the FINAL planet so far found in the system. It is like a larger version of Eeloo, but is scarred in gargantuan crevices and cracks caused by eons of tidal friction. May have a live-supporting subsurface ocean.

 

NIOBE-AMPHION (HD 219134/HR 8832)

Spoiler
  • NIOBE: HD 219134 A, the primary star of the system. It is a K3V orange dwarf with 0.794 times the mass and 80% the radius of Kerbol. Has seven planets in real life, currently has five. It is the second largest star in the mod and is separated from its companion by about 300 million km.
    • EOTIA: HD 219134b, rocky Super-Kerbin with dried lava flows and a diverse, ragged surface. Only a bit of lava. Blue atmosphere of abiotic oxygen,
    • KOLASI: HD 219134 c, molten hellscape with a thick Venusian atmosphere and temperatures nearing 2,000*F.
    • AGNOSTOS: HD 219134 f, iron-rich "Mega Kerbin" with a yellow atmosphere and liquid gallium oceans.
      • AORATOS: Moderate-sized but rather lumpy rock moon in a heavily inclined orbit.
    • NEVERITA: HD 219134 d, a Sudarsky Class III ice giant. It has no clouds, so only a purple globe is revealed.
    • ATMISGI: HD 219134g, a second Mega-Kerbin on the brink of habitability. Multiple seas and golden rings.
      • FENGYMO: Small brown and cream Luna-like satellite orbiting just beyond the rings.
      • MIKROGI: Hot yet habitable desert moon with a thick atmosphere and green plant life.
    • EGERIA: HD 219134 e, giant blue and grey ice planet with huge ravines and kilometers-high ice "spires".
      • NUMA: Tidally heated moon with acidic oceans and air, giant volcanoes, and a scorched surface.
    • NERRIVIK: HD 219134 h, green ice giant with thick icy-blue rings. It seems to have formed similarly to Jool.
      • NK-1: Shepard moon covered in methane ice.
      • NK-3: Oddly colored shepard moon.
      • NK-2: Shepard moon covered in blue ring dust.
      • SANNA: Small reddish ice moon with cryovolcanoes and a thin haze.
      • KOKKSAUT: Green Titan analogue with life and liquid ammonia oceans.
  • AMPHION: HD 219134 B, small red dwarf.

From the surface of Kerbin, both stars are very close in the sky but still destinguishable.

 

CERVANTES (MU ARAE)

Spoiler
  • CERVANTES: Mu Arae, a G3 sub-giant star nearing the end of the main sequence phase. It is about 30% larger than Kerbol and puts out much more light, resulting in an environment very friendly for solar-powered craft. All four of its real-life planets are implemented and have the names given to them by the IAU in 2015. There is also a small comet in the system, along with a huge dusk disk. All 4 planets are currently in the mod.
    • DULCINEA: Mu Arae c, scorched carbon rich Super-Kerbin with lakes of boiling tar. The surface is a hellish 928*K, or 1,211*F, and is coated in a suffocating atmosphere. For those who think Eve is too easy, I challenge you to land on this planet and return to orbit.
    • ROCINANTE: Mu Arae d, yellow gas giant around half the mass of Jool, but a larger radius. Similar in density and composition to real-life Saturn, which could explain its coloring.
      • EHWAZ: Work-in-progress.
    • QUIJOTE: Mu Arae b, habitable zone Super-Jool with rings. It has the most moons in the mod - 3 that naturally formed around it, and 1 captured.
      • LAMANCHA: Kerbin-like moon with oxygen atmosphere, oceans, and continents. The surface has been completely taken over by photosynthetic bacteria.
      • MORENA: Dead rocky moon similar to the Mun. However, it may have once had oceans in the past.
      • PERSILES: Desert moon with purple bacteria covering most of the surface. Has a breathable atmosphere.
      • BARCELON: Captured oceanic moon with huge ice caps and a diversity of aquatic life.
    • SANCHO: Mu Arae e, large gas giant with ammonia clouds. It is the most similar to real-life Jupiter.
      • GALATEA: Desert moon with a breathable atmosphere.
      • ELASTRO: Tiny ice moon; has an oxygen atmosphere and cryovolcanic geysers.
      • ELICIO: Huge, captured ice planet with a large impact basin and a debris field.
        • MARCIA: Work-in-progress.
      • DARANI: Heavily cratered brown ice moon.
    • KALLEY: Small green comet with a long orbital period.

 

K2-3

Spoiler
  • K2-3: A rather large red dwarf of spectral type M0V. It is a rather near star that is over half the size and mass of Kerbol. The star is surrounded by three planets in real life - all currently in the mod. While it is once of the largest M-dwarfs ever found, its sunlight is still very dim. What's also odd is how metal poor it is, which is shocking because the third planet is an iron world.
    • PHOCYS: K2-3b, a large hot ocean planet with a thick atmosphere. A few tiny islands are visible.
    • BRIGID: K2-3c, mint colored gas dwarf. It is suffering from atmospheric loss and thus has the second-thinnest atmosphere in the system - which is still 5 times thicker than Kerbin's.
    • GALENE: K2-3d, iron planet with lowlands of Ice-VII. It is 96% metals and has almost 5 times the gravity of Kerbin. Thus, it has a thick atmosphere.
      • GLAUCE: Duna-sized moon with atmosphere and oceans. Also iron-rich.
      • CINYRAS: Captured dwarf planet in orbit around Galene. It may have started as a planet that was smashed by Galene billions of years ago.

 

LICH (PSR B1257+12)

Spoiler
  • LICH: PSR B1257+12, a rapidly rotating pulsar spewing out radiation and circled by a ring of debris. It has three planets in real life, one currently in the mod.
    • DRAUGR: Mun-sized planet with lowlands and craters filled with diamonds.

 

 

UPCOMING FEATURES!

While at version 1.2.9, IA-Revived has quite a lot of work ahead. Here are the features coming up soon. Those in green will be in the next update (1.3.0), those in blue in near-future versions, features in orange and coming later on, and those in red are...dubious.

  • Completing the rest of the 1.3.0 features.
  • Completion of the Lich system.
  • Biomes! Biomes! Biomes!
  • Working with Sigma Binary
  • The Kepler-47 system

DEVELOPMENT STATUS (AUGUST 18th)

  • Pre-release 1.2.9 has been uploaded to Spacedock. Development on 1.3.0 will re-continue in a few weeks, after my trip to the Carolinas and the busy end-of-summer schedule.

Fun Facts/Tips:

  • Glauce is the only moon in the mod that may be detectable in real life, if such a moon like it exists.
  • Braciaca is inspired by a study in late 2016 proving that the majority of rogue planets are frozen, orphaned Mars-sized worlds.
  • Morena has a pretty small SOI. It is best not to encounter it with an eccentric orbit, or else you will fly by it too quickly to be captured.
  • There were plans to make a new moon for Selphar, named Valgoh. However, I scrapped the idea when its height map was glitching up.
  • Barcelon may be the new nesting place of the Kraken. Be warned.
  • All planets orbit at 1/10th the distance they do in real life.
  • Every planet and moon is 1/10th the size they would be in real life. However, the star sizes are proportional to Kerbol as they are to the Sun in real life.
  • All main system stars are 1/1000th the distance they are in reality.
  • The name for Trappist-1f was partially inspired by Hurricane Irene, a tropical cyclone that proved quite a nuisance for me back in 2011.
  • During initial development, Cervantes was known as Alcides and the planets were named Iolaus, Iphicles, Hylas, and Megara. I may use those names for any planetary systems I find in the Hercules constellation.
  • Lamancha went through FIVE re-texturings during the development of version 1.1.0. In fact, I did ANOTHER re-texture for 1.2.9/1.3.0.

I've done some more testing and object creation. Say hello to Numa, the replacement moon for Manius. It is an atmosphere-less, greenish desert moon with a unique surface chemistry and very primitive bacteria. Almost seems like some other race contaminated the moon years ago and allowed hardy bacteria to spread all over. With Sigma Simentions it can be accomplished the following way: 

@Kopernicus:BEFORE[SigDim2]
{
	@Body:HAS[@Orbit:HAS[#referenceBody[Sun],#semiMajorAxis[>13e9]]]
	{
		@SigmaDimensions
		{
			@Rescale *= X
		}
	}
}

It may just be that this mod is too big for your computer to handle. I recommend using KSP x64 bit. But here's an install instruction:

  1. Download from SpaceDock (link in OP)
  2. Extract the contents of the zip file.
  3. In the new IA-Revived file, there is a gamedata file. Go in there and you will find everything you need. Copy and paste all the folders into KSP's GameData folder.
  4. Done! Time to test to see if it works.
